        <h1>Energy: monitoring consumption</h1>
        <p>Read consumption statistics appear in the <b>Dashboard</b> page. From here you can view the consumption and costs of each group and their percent of total site consumption. By analyzing the graph you can decide whether a group can be connected to a control meter that can be turned on by programming time slots in <span style="font-weight: bold;"><a href="Calendario_impianto__introduzione.htm">Plant calendar</a></span>. </p>
        <p class="Image">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/Energy_file/Sinottico_506x300.png" style="border: none;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;width: 506;height: 300;" border="0" />
        </p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />Stopping Energy                         </p>
        <p>Energy must be stopped before you create/delete a meter group.</p>
        <ul>
            <li value="1">To stop Energy, in the <b>Dashboard</b> page click <img id="_x0000_i1054" src="../Resources/Images/actions/stop_button.png" style="border-style: none;width: 24px;height: 24px;float: none;" width="24" height="24" border="0" /> <b>Stop</b>: Energy pauses statistic analyses.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />Starting Energy                       </p>
        <p>This is required after you create/delete a meter group.</p>
        <ul>
            <li value="1">To start Energy, in the <b>Dashboard</b> page click <img src="../Resources/Images/actions/Start_button.png" style="border-style: none;width: 24px;height: 24px;float: none;" width="24" height="24" border="0" /> <b>Start</b>: Energy analyzes data read in real-time by PlantVisorPRO and displays them.</li>
        </ul>
        <table style="width: 100%;border-left-color: #000000;border-left-width: 1px;border-right-color: #000000;border-right-width: 1px;background-color: #c0c0c0;border-spacing: 0px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#C0C0C0" width="100%">
            <col style="width: 72px;" />
            <col />
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" valign="middle">
                    <p class="Note">
                        <img src="../Resources/Images/AAinfo.gif" style="border: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />
                    </p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="padding-right: 1px;padding-left: 1px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 2px;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC">
                    <p>If a meter was just added to a group, it may not have recorded values yet. Wait several minutes (i.e.: 15 minutes) to have a good number of valid readings.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />Clearing meter data                        </p>
        <p>Clearing data lets you start monitoring from zero in terms of consumption and costs.</p>
        <p>Clearing data does not physically delete meter counters but only the data collected in Energy.</p>
        <ul>
            <li value="1">To do this, in the <b>Dashboard</b> page select the meters or groups to be cleared and click <b>Reset</b>.</li>
        </ul>
